params.message:
Simplify: Part of the expression is unnecessary

37|     -- if condition can be simplified to 0
38|     Nothing -> if (True && False) then 1 else 0
                       ^^^^^^^^^^^^^

A part of this condition is unnecessary. You can remove it and it would not impact the behavior of the program.

Simplify: Condition is always False

37|     -- if condition can be simplified to 0
38|     Nothing -> if (True && False) then 1 else 0
                       ^^^^^^^^^^^^^

This condition will always result in the same value. You may have hardcoded a value or mistyped a condition.

Simplify: Unnecessary multiplication by 1

34|     -- something is unused
35|     Just something -> 1 * 1
                           ^^^^
36|     -- True && False can be simplified to False

Multiplying by 1 does not change the value of the number.

Value `something` is not used.

You should either use this value somewhere or replace it with '_'.

Parameter `unused` is not used

You should either use it somewhere, or remove it.

Imported variable `withDefault` is not used

You should either use it somewhere, or remove it.

Imported module `Parser.Advanced` is not used

You should either use it somewhere, or remove it.

Argument is never extracted and therefore never used.

You should either use it somewhere, or remove it.

Type constructor `Nope` is not used.

It might be handled everywhere it might appear, but there is no location where this value actually gets created.
